    "body": "I ran about 100,000,000 continuous RPC requests over about a four hour period. Mix of `eth_getTrans...`, `eth_getReceipt`, and `eth_blockNumber`. Not a great test, but no crash. It would be nice to find a way to some real stress testing.\r\n\r\nI found through a Google search that `crashed: rpc error: code = Canceled desc = context canceled goroutine` may have something to do with the request taking too long (timing out).\r\n\r\nJust a theory, but if that's the case, perhaps the issue is poor error reporting. Perhaps on a time out it should just report a time out and not a stack trace.",
